cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.CY, cs.SI

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the analysis of textual corpora. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves the extraction of trends from textual data. Additionally, the use of scalable algorithms suggests a connection to cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and the ever-increasing number of born-digital documents points towards cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the comparison of trends across different corpora could be related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
